hdn:TextFragment rdf:type owl:Class .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#Citation_Signalling
ConnectiveOntology:Citation_Signalling rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf cidoc-crm:E55_Type ;
                                       rdfs:comment """Denotes the type of textual signalling, i.e. whether or not the text tells us it is referring to something external of itself.

Examples:

\"As David said [...]\" = specificPersonalSignalling
\"As the Bible says\" = genericTextualSignalling
\"As a wise man once said\" = genericPersonalSignalling
\"As is written in Corinthians 2.4 \" = specificTextualSignalling

Personal and textual signalling can of course be combined, e.g.:

\"As the Apostle says in Corinthians 2,4\" = specificTextualSignalling and  specificPersonalSignalling"""@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Citation Signalling"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#Claim
ConnectiveOntology:Claim rdf:type owl:Class ;
                         rdfs:subClassOf cidoc-crm:E73_Information_Object ;
                         rdfs:comment "A speech act that includes assertion by the speaker that they consider this utterance to be true."@en ;
                         rdfs:label "Claim"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#Comment
ConnectiveOntology:Comment rdf:type owl:Class ;
                           rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:ConnectiveClaim ;
                           rdfs:comment "Comment added by an editor which connects the subject to a certain interpretation without pointing to an external resource."@en ;
                           rdfs:label "Comment"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#ConnectiveClaim
ConnectiveOntology:ConnectiveClaim rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:Claim ;
                                   rdfs:comment """A Connective Claim proposes that \"knowledge about x can be enriched through considering y\", where

- x is the subject of the claim (generally a text passage)
- y is the object of the claim (a text passage, a motif, a location)

Connective claims are often uttered in scholarly contexts, for example when identifying a citation or a reference.

Connective claim is equivalent to the class hdn:Reference."""@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Connective Claim"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#ParallelType
ConnectiveOntology:ParallelType rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                rdfs:subClassOf cidoc-crm:E55_Type ;
                                rdfs:comment "Further specifies a Textual or Topical Parallel by assigning is a type. The type usually states how close the subject and the object are to each other from 'Verbatim', i.e. word-for-word identical, to a 'LooseRendering', which makes them very different."@en ;
                                rdfs:label "Textual parallel type"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#ParallelinOtherLanguage
ConnectiveOntology:ParallelinOtherLanguage rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                           rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:TextualParallel ;
                                           rdfs:comment """Subcategory of a Textual Parallel which signifies that the object (the text where the connection is drawn towards) is in another language than the subject (the text the connection is drawn from). 

Is aligned with SAWS predicate \"IsVersionInAnotherLanguageOf\" and can be combined with a Type assignment, which then replaces the predicates:

'isVerbatimTranslationOf ', 'isVariantTranslationOf', and so forth."""@en ;
                                           rdfs:label "Parallel in other language"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#ParallelinSameLanguage
ConnectiveOntology:ParallelinSameLanguage rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                          rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:TextualParallel ;
                                          rdfs:comment """Subcategory of a Textual Parallel which signifies that the object (the text where the connection is drawn towards) is in the same language as the subject (the text the connection is drawn from). 

Can be combined with a Type assignment such as \"VerbatimofText\" or 'VariantOfText' to express the SAWS predicates: 'isVerbatimOf ', 'isVariantOf', and so on."""@en ;
                                          rdfs:label "Parallel in same Language"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#RenderingOfText
ConnectiveOntology:RenderingOfText rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:ParallelinSameLanguage ;
                                   rdfs:comment """Subclass of a Textual parallel in the same language, which indicates that something is expressed \"in a related but different way\". Abstraction of the two SAWS subtypes \"closeRendering\" and \"looseRendering\". Defined as:

\"This property specifies the source and target LinguisticObject involved (respectively) when rendering one LinguisticObject instance to express it in a related but different way (not necessarily in a different Language), resulting in a new LinguisticObject e.g. poetry into prose, or from one dialect to another, or a paraphrase being made.\""""@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Rendering of text"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#Statement
ConnectiveOntology:Statement rdf:type owl:Class ;
                             rdfs:subClassOf lrmoo:F1_Work ;
                             rdfs:comment "General, abstracted type of discursive statements, e.g. \"Muhammad was not a true prophet\" or \"Jesus was not truly crucified\", which can be realized in different concrete formulations."@en ;
                             rdfs:label "Statement"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#StatementExpression
ConnectiveOntology:StatementExpression rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                       rdfs:subClassOf lrmoo:F2_Expression ;
                                       rdfs:comment "A concrete expression of an argument Archtype. Realised in statement formulations."@en ;
                                       rdfs:label "Statement expression"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#TextualParallel
ConnectiveOntology:TextualParallel rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf hdn:LociParalleli ;
                                   rdfs:comment "Subclass of a Connective Claim that indicates some textual similarity between the subject and the object, which can be specified by further subclasses and type assigments."@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Textual parallel"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#TopicalParallel
ConnectiveOntology:TopicalParallel rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                   rdfs:subClassOf hdn:LociParalleli ;
                                   rdfs:comment "Type of Connective Claim that signals a Topical Parallel between the subject and the object that thereby claims no textual overlap. Most Textual Parallels will also be Topical Parallels, but not vice versa."@en ;
                                   rdfs:label "Topical parallel"@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#VariantOfText
ConnectiveOntology:VariantOfText rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:VersionOfText .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#VerbatimOfText
ConnectiveOntology:VerbatimOfText rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                  rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:VersionOfText .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#VersionOfText
ConnectiveOntology:VersionOfText rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                 rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:ParallelinSameLanguage .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#explicitSignalling
ConnectiveOntology:explicitSignalling rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                      rdfs:subClassOf ConnectiveOntology:Citation_Signalling ;
                                      rdfs:comment "Subclass of Citation Signalling, which indicates that the author of a text makes it explicit that some citation or re-use is happening. Can be further specified by types."@en ;
                                      rdfs:label "Explicit signalling"@en .


#################################################################
#    Individuals
#################################################################

###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#Allusion
ConnectiveOntology:Allusion rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                     ConnectiveOntology:Citation_Signalling ;
                            rdfs:comment "Type of Citation Signalling. The reader receives some hints that the text is a quotation, but the source is only alluded to."@en .


###  https://otraorg.github.io/ontology#CloseRenderingOfText
ConnectiveOntology:CloseRenderingOfText rdf:type owl:NamedIndividual ,
                                                 ConnectiveOntology:ParallelType ;
                                        rdfs:comment """Type of Connective Claim that is aligned with the SAWS predicate \"isCloseRenderingOf\", which is defined as:

