ConnectiveOntology:VariantOfText rdfs:comment """Subclass of Textual Version that indicates how closely related two passages of text are. Aligned with the SAWS predicate \"isVariantOf\", defined as:

\"A LinguisticObject is a linguistically modified copy of a second LinguisticObject, in the same language/genre, and of the same length, with only small variation in use or order of words, e.g. one or two words substituted for another, or a connective inserted. This may or may not have different conceptual function. This need not imply that one is a direct copy of the other, nor which is the earlier\""""@en ;
                                 rdfs:label "Variant of text"@en .


ConnectiveOntology:VerbatimOfText rdfs:comment """Type of Textual Parallel that indicates a very close connection between subject and object. Aligned with the SAWS predicates

\"isVerbatimOfText\": \"A LinguisticObject is a verbatim, word-for-word copy of another LinguisticObject. This need not imply that one is a direct copy of the other, nor which is the earlier\"
\"isVerbatimTranslationOf \": \"word-for-word translation (ad pedem). This need not imply that one is a direct translation of the other, nor which is the earlier\""""@en ;
                                  rdfs:label "Verbatim of text"@en .


ConnectiveOntology:VersionOfText rdfs:comment """Subclass of a Textual Parallel that is aligned with the SAWS predicate \"isVersionOf\". Defined as:

\"A LinguisticObject is a version in the same language of another LinguisticObject. This relates to the other object, but matches less closely than isVariantOf. This need not imply that one is a direct copy of the other, nor which is the earlier.\""""@en ;
                                 rdfs:label "Version of text"@en .


